Yes this makes sense because it is easier to measure bird eggs than it is to measure mammal eggs, but Im not sure about the reptile egg missing variables.
"Yes this makes sense because it is easier to measure bird eggs than it is to measure mammal eggs, but Im not sure about the reptile egg missing variables."
amniota.nas %>%
group_by(class) %>%
select(class, egg_mass_g) %>%
miss_var_summary() %>%
arrange(desc(n_miss))
"Yes this makes sense because it is easier to measure bird eggs than it is to measure mammal eggs, but Im not sure about the reptile egg missing variables. My interpretation of NAs is that they can also be used not only as a way to express a lack of measurements, but also they can be used if we are physically unable to measure certain variables, like mammal eggs."
